gov.va.vinci.leo.ae

Class LeoBaseAnnotator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.uima.analysis_component.AnalysisComponent_ImplBase
      • org.apache.uima.analysis_component.Annotator_ImplBase
        • org.apache.uima.analysis_component.JCasAnnotator_ImplBase
          • gov.va.vinci.leo.ae.LeoBaseAnnotator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LeoAnnotator, org.apache.uima.analysis_component.AnalysisComponent
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LeoCachingAnnotator

    public abstract class LeoBaseAnnotator
extends org.apache.uima.analysis_component.JCasAnnotator_ImplBase
implements LeoAnnotator
    Base annotator class for holding functions that all annotators might take advantage of, such as loading resource files, etc.

    Note: This base class assumes a string[] parameter of input types and a string output type in the uima parameters to know what input types to use and what output type to create.

      • hasFilteredAnnotation

        protected boolean hasFilteredAnnotation(org.apache.uima.jcas.JCas jCas)
                                 throws org.apache.uima.analysis_engine.AnalysisEngineProcessException
        If includeTypesFilter is not set then return true. If there is a includeTypesFilter and includeFilter is true then return true only if one of the includeTypesFilter types have been found and false if not. If includeFilter is false then return true when all of the types in the filter list have not been found or true otherwise.
        Parameters:
        jCas - CAS to check for filtered types
        Returns:
        true if the filter is met, false otherwise
        Throws:
        org.apache.uima.analysis_engine.AnalysisEngineProcessException - if one of the type names in the tyepsFilter is not found in the type system

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if types are found, false otherwise
        Throws:

      • containsAnnotationInList

        protected boolean containsAnnotationInList(org.apache.uima.jcas.JCas jCas,
                                           String[] typeList,
                                           boolean isEmpty)
                                    throws org.apache.uima.analysis_engine.AnalysisEngineProcessException
        Checks the CAS for instances of the annotation types in the list. If the list is empty return the value of the isEmpty flag.
        Parameters:
        jCas - CAS to check
        typeList - list of types to check for
        isEmpty - if this list is empty then return the value of this boolean flag
        Returns:
        true if a type instance if found, false if not found, isEmpty if the list is empty
        Throws:
        org.apache.uima.analysis_engine.AnalysisEngineProcessException - If one of the types is not in the type system of the CAS
